CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "1953 Debutantes...Pictured, the Debutantes of 1953, following their presentation Monday night at Syria Mosque, where sorors of Alpha Kappa Alpha gave their annual Cotillion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twenty-one debutantes wearing light colored strapless gowns, four flower girls, and two girls wearing costumes, posed in Syria Mosque for the 1953 Alpha Kappa Alpha cotillion
